                        <h2 class="faq_h2">Getting Started<i class="fas fa-angle-right faq_blue_right_arrow"></i><i class="fas fa-angle-down faq_blue_down_arrow"></i></h2>
                        <p class="faq_sub_header_title">You can view content in our public section without registration. However you are required to register to use the full features of Tourist Tube.</p>
                        <h3 class="help_h3">registration</h3>
                        <p class="faq_sub_header_title">Fill in and submit the registration form with all the required fields and we will promptly set up your account and send you a confirmation email.</p>
                        <h3 class="help_h3">login</h3>
                        <p class="faq_sub_header_title">Use your username and password to login. If you like to automatically login upon landing, check the tick box. In the event you forget your password, fill in and submit your email or username and we will send a password reset order to your email.</p>
                        <h3 class="help_h3">mobile</h3>
                        <p class="faq_sub_header_title">You can freely download and install Tourist Tube mobile application on your Android mobile.</p>
                        <h3 class="help_h3">search</h3>
                        <p class="faq_sub_header_title">You can use the search bar to search all media in Tourist Tube using particular keywords or a combination thereof.You can narrow your search by selecting to search only photos, videos, hotels, restaurants, or Tubers.</p>
                        <h3 class="help_h3">upload</h3>
                        <p class="faq_sub_header_title">Once you are registered, you can upload up to 1 Tera-byte of photos and videos to your account. For each upload, you can add descriptors such as title, keywords, place, theme or category, and your comments; also for each upload, you can control privacy settings for views, likes, and comments among public (everybody), friends and their connections, friends, or private (only you).</p>
                        <h3 class="help_h3">chat</h3>
                        <p class="faq_sub_header_title">Once you are registered, you can use the chat window to chat with other Tubers and to search for / add / delete Tubers. You can also disable / enable this window.</p>
